genresAdvancedInfo.name: japanese concert band
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Japanese concert band, also known as wind band or symphonic band, is a popular music genre in Japan. It is characterized by the use of wind and percussion instruments such as the flute, clarinet, trumpet, trombone, and percussion. The music is often performed in outdoor settings such as parks and festivals, and it is known for its lively and energetic sound.
